<% @page_title = "Privacy Policy" %>

<div class="min-width center pad" style="max-width: 720px; padding: 2rem 1rem;">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="translucent"><em>Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></em></p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy describes how Campfire ("we", "our", or "us") processes your information when you use our mobile application.</p>

  <h2>Data Controller</h2>
  <p>The data controller responsible for your information is Campfire. You can contact us at: <strong>your@email.com</strong></p>

  <h2>Permissions We Request</h2>

  <h3>Camera and Microphone</h3>
  <p>We request access to your device’s camera and microphone solely to enable video and voice communication within the app.</p>

  <p>Audio and video communication is conducted through external servers configured by the user (for example, Jitsi-compatible servers). We do not operate or control these servers.</p>

  <p>Media data (audio and video) is transmitted in real time during calls and is not recorded or stored by us. The handling of such data by external servers depends on their respective privacy and security practices.</p>

  <h3>Notifications</h3>
  <p>We request permission to send push notifications related to messages and activity. You can disable notifications at any time in your device settings.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect only the information necessary to provide the service, such as your name, email address, and account-related data.</p>

  <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>We use your information to operate, maintain, and improve the application. Processing is based on performance of a contract and our legitimate interests in providing the service.</p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data.</p>

  <p>For real-time communication features, the app connects to third-party or user-provided servers (such as Jitsi-compatible servers). These servers may process audio and video data as part of providing communication functionality. We do not control these servers and are not responsible for their data handling practices.</p>

  <p>We may also rely on infrastructure providers (such as hosting or networking services) strictly to operate the application.</p>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>Your account and message data are stored securely. Media from calls is not stored by us after the session ends.</p>

  <h2>User Responsibility</h2>
  <p>Users are responsible for configuring and managing their own communication servers and ensuring compliance with applicable laws and privacy requirements.</p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data. To exercise these rights, contact us using the email below.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at: <strong>daiji@daiwick.com</strong></p>
</div>
